President Biden and Chancellor Scholz of Germany met at the White House to strengthen U.S.-German relations and deepen the transatlantic partnership. They discussed diplomatic and deterrence efforts in response to Russia's military build-up on Ukraine's borders, supporting Ukraine's sovereignty, and preventing Russia from using energy as a weapon. The leaders also talked about Germany's G7 Presidency and joint actions to end the COVID-19 pandemic, address the climate crisis, and promote global economic recovery. They pledged to cooperate on challenges posed by China and support stability in the Western Balkans.